                <h1>Who Wrote "Go Tell It on the Mountain"?</h1>
                <p>"Go Tell It on the Mountain," published in 1953, is a semi-autobiographical novel written by James Baldwin. It explores themes of identity, religion, and family through the coming-of-age story of a young African American boy named John Grimes in 1930s Harlem. Baldwin's powerful prose captures the struggles and aspirations of his characters, reflecting his own experiences.</p>
